#. <section class="sutta" id="sn18.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn18.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 18"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 18"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn18.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 11. Cakkhusutta → cakkhuādisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn18.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Cakkhusutta"
msgstr "11. The Eye, Etc."

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.250"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn18.11:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ "
"bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one "
"side. The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Rāhula? "

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.5"
msgid "cakkhuṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.6"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.7"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.8"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.9"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.10"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.11"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.12"
msgid "“Sotaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "“… the ear …"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.13"
msgid "ghānaṃ …"
msgstr "the nose …"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.14"
msgid "jivhā …"
msgstr "the tongue …"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.15"
msgid "kāyo …"
msgstr "the body …"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.16"
msgid "mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the mind permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.17"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.18"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.19"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.20"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.21"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.22"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.23"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … "
"sotasmimpi nibbindati … ghānasmimpi nibbindati … jivhāyapi nibbindati … "
"kāyasmimpi nibbindati … manasmimpi nibbindati;"
msgstr ""
"“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, the "
"ear, the nose, the tongue, the body, and the mind."

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.24"
msgid ""
"nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.25"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

msgctxt "sn18.11:1.26"
msgid "(Etena peyyālena dasa suttantā kātabbā.)"
msgstr "(The ten discourses of this series should be treated in the same way.)"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn18.11:1.27"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
